main event: Radar detected two objects, one large and one small, maneuvering and giving a bright and steady radar return over Gardnerville, Nevada on July 27, 1961.
interesting points: The objects were detected by radar, but no visual sighting was obtained.
The radar showed the objects maneuvering and giving a bright and steady return.
One object was described as large, while the other was smaller.
The sighting lasted for approximately 2 minutes.
The location was near Gardnerville, Nevada.
sighted object: two unidentified objects detected on radar
